OL,3,C'Beloved' Scottish Borders railway
OL,4,Ccampaigner dies at the age of 95
OL,6,F"She loved Wilton Park and spent so
OL,7,Fmuch time at the tennis courts,
OL,8,Fplaying, coaching, organising juniors,
OL,9,Fmatches and competitions, as well as
OL,10,Fmanaging the courts when the council
OL,11,Fwould no longer provide a court
OL,12,Fattendant.
OL,14,F"She loved to see young people playing
OL,15,Fsport. We're very glad she was able to
OL,16,Fattend the re-opening of Teviot Day
OL,17,FService a few weeks ago, the last
OL,18,Fcampaign she was involved in.
OL,20,F"We will certainly miss her."
